<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1436,1727,2034]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,261,1727,1753]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Content:</emphasis>
Two subspecies restricted to the 
<collectingRegion box="[659,848,1728,1754]" country="Chile" name="Atacama" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Atacama Desert</collectingRegion>
in northern 
<collectingCountry box="[996,1060,1728,1754]" name="Chile" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Chile</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Donoso-Barros" box="[1077,1340,1728,1754]" firstAuthor="Donoso-Barros" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" refId="ref57808" refString="Donoso-Barros, R. (1966 a) Reptiles de Chile. Ediciones de la Universidad de Chile, Santiago, 458 pp." type="book" year="1966" yearSuffix="a">Donoso-Barros 1966a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Donoso-Barros" box="[1354,1431,1728,1754]" firstAuthor="Donoso-Barros" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="49 - 124" refId="ref58063" refString="Donoso-Barros, R. (1970 b) Catalogo herpetologico chileno. Boletin del Museo Nacional de Historia Natural de Chile, 31, 49 - 124." type="journal article" year="1970" yearSuffix="b">1970b</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Cei" box="[151,267,1768,1794]" firstAuthor="Cei" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" refId="ref54875" refString="Cei, J. M. (1993) Reptiles del noroeste, nordeste y este de la Argentina. Herpetofauna de las selvas subtropicales, Puna y Pampas. Museo Regionale di Scienze Naturali di Torino, Monografie 14, 949 pp." type="book" year="1993">Cei 1993</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Pincheira-Donoso &amp; Nunez" box="[284,696,1768,1794]" firstAuthor="Pincheira-Donoso" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" refId="ref69923" refString="Pincheira-Donoso, D. &amp; Nunez, H. (2005) Las especies chilenas del genero Liolaemus (Iguania, Tropiduridae, Liolaeminae). Taxonomia, sistematica y evolucion, Publicacion Ocasional del Museo Nacional de Historia Natural de Chile, Santiago, 486 pp." type="book" year="2005">Pincheira-Donoso &amp; Núñez 2005</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Pincheira-Donoso, D." box="[713,1001,1768,1794]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="93 - 150" refId="ref69621" refString="Pincheira-Donoso, D. (2005) Anfibios y reptiles de la Provincia de El Loa. In: Ramirez, G. M. &amp; Pincheira-Donoso, D. (Ed.), Fauna del Altiplano y Desierto de Atacama. Vertebrados de la Provincia de El Loa. Phrynosaura Ediciones, Calama, 93 - 150." type="book chapter" year="2005">Pincheira-Donoso 2005</bibRefCitation>
). Although 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ortiz" authorityYear="1975" box="[1150,1378,1768,1793]" class="Reptilia" family="Liolaemidae" genus="Liolaemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="donosoi">
<emphasis box="[1150,1378,1768,1793]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Liolaemus donosoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was recently resurrected as a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Donoso-Barros" authorityYear="1961" box="[610,772,1808,1833]" class="Reptilia" family="Liolaemidae" genus="Liolaemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="constanzae">
<emphasis box="[610,772,1808,1833]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">L. constanzae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Pincheira-Donoso &amp; Nunez" box="[787,1186,1808,1834]" firstAuthor="Pincheira-Donoso" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" refId="ref69923" refString="Pincheira-Donoso, D. &amp; Nunez, H. (2005) Las especies chilenas del genero Liolaemus (Iguania, Tropiduridae, Liolaeminae). Taxonomia, sistematica y evolucion, Publicacion Ocasional del Museo Nacional de Historia Natural de Chile, Santiago, 486 pp." type="book" year="2005">Pincheira-Donoso &amp; Núñez 2005</bibRefCitation>
; see previous discussions in 
<bibRefCitation author="Nunez &amp; Jaksic" box="[248,503,1848,1874]" firstAuthor="Nunez" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="63 - 91" refId="ref67479" refString="Nunez, H. &amp; Jaksic, F. M. (1992) Lista comentada de los reptiles terrestres de Chile continental. Boletin del Museo Nacional de Historia Natural de Chile, 43, 63 - 91." type="journal article" year="1992">Núñez &amp; Jaksic 1992</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Etheridge &amp; Espinoza" box="[515,844,1848,1874]" firstAuthor="Etheridge" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="1 - 64" refId="ref59521" refString="Etheridge, R &amp; Espinoza, R. E. (2000) Taxonomy of the Liolaeminae (Squamata: Iguania: Tropiduridae) and a semiannotated bibliography. Smithsonian Herpetological Information Service, 126, 1 - 64." type="journal article" year="2000">Etheridge &amp; Espinoza 2000</bibRefCitation>
), it is still needed to evaluate with modern analytical procedures (
<emphasis box="[357,400,1888,1913]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">e.g.</emphasis>
molecular variables) the status of these two taxa. Indeed, at this time, limited morphological data and their fully isolated geographical ranges (separated by the preandean Domeyko mountain chain; see 
<bibRefCitation author="Ramirez &amp; Pincheira-Donoso" box="[326,742,1968,1994]" firstAuthor="Ramirez" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="350 - 365" refId="ref70018" refString="Pincheira-Donoso, D. &amp; Ramirez, G. M. (2005) Desplazamiento de caracteres como evidencias de un posible caso de especiacion simpatrica entre dos Liolaemus del grupo jamesi en la Provincia de El Loa, con la descripcion de una nueva especie. In: Ramirez, G. M. &amp; Pincheira-Donoso, D. (Ed.), Fauna del Altiplano y Desierto de Atacama. Vertebrados de la Provincia de El Loa. Phrynosaura Ediciones, Calama, 350 - 365." type="book chapter" year="2005">Ramírez &amp; Pincheira-Donoso 2005</bibRefCitation>
) are the only available evidence supporting the subspecific rank of these lizards.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
